dataList.title: La Manchaland
dataList.content: Long have I not set foot upon the earth.
Even now, you remain ensnared to your responsibilities, unable to flee!

dataList.title: La Manchaland
dataList.content: Where must I flee to, then? Enlighten me, Sancho.

dataList.title: La Manchaland
dataList.content: I tipped the scales of that endless war, yet... there was no coexistence to be found at its end.

dataList.title: La Manchaland
dataList.content: With blood, I have created this place, yet no family has found happiness within it.

dataList.title: La Manchaland
dataList.content: I have dreamed, yet the dream only woke me to a heart impaled by stakes and this fetid stench of blood. Look at me, Sancho!

dataList.title: La Manchaland
dataList.content: I am but Don Quixote... La Manchaland's Don Quixote.
